race.description: Crjc Christmas Race Day Country Boosted Hcp (C2)
race.comment: RISK FOR REWARD (5) took charge in the early stages then never gave his rivals a look in last start over 1590m at Ballina. Doesn't win too often but those bold tactics last start paid off so a repeat is definitely on the cards. NEXT PAY RUN (4) has found the line well without threatening in her two runs this prep, the latest over 1300m at Ballina. Suited by the extra 110m at this stage of the campaign. Races well here and poses a genuine threat. AMARONE (3) savaged the line but just missed over 1450m at Muswellbrook most recently. Enjoys a soft run from the inside alley and will be tough to hold out when presented. GOT THE SMARTS (7) gets back in her races but has placed four from five at Grafton so she is right in the mix. Watch for a better run today from TIETAR (2) with blinkers applied for the first time.
